---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/docs.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Privacy Policy — Airlock">
    <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="text-muted-foreground mt-1">Last updated: March 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">1. Overview</h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    Airlock is a cryptographic approval gateway for AI agents.
                    Privacy is a core architectural principle — the system is
                    designed so that <strong
                        >Airlock never sees the content of AI actions</strong
                    >. This document explains what data we collect, how we
                    process it, and your rights.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    2. Zero-Knowledge Architecture
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    Airlock's Gateway operates as a zero-knowledge relay. All AI
                    action payloads are <strong>encrypted end-to-end</strong> between
                    the enforcer (your IDE) and the approver (your mobile device)
                    using AES-256-GCM. The Gateway only processes opaque ciphertext
                    — it cannot decrypt, read, or store the content of AI actions.
                </p>
                <div
                    class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-border/50 bg-muted/30 mt-4"
                >
                    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                        <strong class="text-foreground"
                            >What the Gateway sees:</strong
                        > Request metadata (timestamps, artifact type, request IDs,
                        enforcer IDs). <br />
                        <strong class="text-foreground"
                            >What the Gateway never sees:</strong
                        > AI command content, file diffs, terminal output, source
                        code, or any payload data.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    3. Data We Collect
                </h2>

                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">3.1 Account Data</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    When you create an account, we collect:
                </p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-muted-foreground mt-2">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Email
                        address (for authentication and account recovery)
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Display
                        name (optional)
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span
                        >Authentication credentials (hashed, never stored in
                        plaintext)
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">3.2 Device Data</h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    When you pair a mobile device, we store:
                </p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-muted-foreground mt-2">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Device
                        token (for push notifications via Firebase Cloud
                        Messaging)
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Ed25519
                        public key (for signature verification)
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Device name
                        and platform (for display in the admin console)
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">
                    3.3 Workspace & Approval Metadata
                </h3>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    We store operational metadata:
                </p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-muted-foreground mt-2">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Workspace
                        names and configuration
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Approval
                        request timestamps and status
                        (approved/rejected/expired)
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span>Artifact
                        type labels (e.g., "terminal_command") — <strong
                            >not</strong
                        > the command content
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">
                    3.4 Data We Do NOT Collect
                </h3>
                <div
                    class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-500/5 mt-2"
                >
                    <ul class="space-y-1 text-muted-foreground text-sm">
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✗</span>AI command
                            content or terminal output
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✗</span>Source
                            code or file diffs
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✗</span>Encryption
                            keys or private signing keys
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✗</span>Browsing
                            history or usage analytics
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                            <span class="text-green-500 mt-1">✗</span>Repository
                            contents or project metadata
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    4. Push Notifications
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    When an approval request arrives, we send a push
                    notification via Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM). These
                    notifications contain <strong
                        >only the request ID and artifact type</strong
                    > — no payload content. The mobile app then fetches the encrypted
                    artifact directly from the Gateway and decrypts it locally.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    5. Data Retention
                </h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    Approval request metadata is retained for audit purposes.
                    Encrypted artifacts on the Gateway are ephemeral and
                    automatically purged after the approval decision is made or
                    the request expires. You may request deletion of your
                    account and all associated data at any time.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">
                    6. Third-Party Services
                </h2>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >Firebase Cloud Messaging:</strong
                        > Push notification delivery (Google's privacy policy applies)
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >Google Sign-In:</strong
                        > Optional authentication provider (if you choose to sign
                        in with Google)
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                        <span class="text-link mt-1">•</span><strong
                            >GitHub Sign-In:</strong
                        > Optional authentication provider (if you choose to sign
                        in with GitHub)
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">7. Your Rights</h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    You have the right to access, correct, or delete your
                    personal data. You may also request a copy of all data
                    associated with your account. To exercise these rights,
                    contact us at the email provided in your account settings.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-3">8. Contact</h2>
                <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                    For privacy-related inquiries, please contact us through the
                    information provided in your Airlock account or on our
                    website.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 flex gap-4">
            <a href="/docs" class="text-sm text-link hover:underline"
                >← All Docs</a
            >
            <a href="/" class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:underline"
                >Back to Airlock</a
            >
        </div>
    </div>
</DocsLayout>
